---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Press Release: 300th Colony Milestone"
  description="Weyland-Yutani Corporation celebrates the establishment of its 300th colony, reflecting on eight decades of interstellar expansion and the future of human settlement."
  type="article"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="bg-black pt-36">
    <!-- ARTICLE HEADER -->
    <section class="relative py-20 border-b border-[#1a1a1a]">
      <div class="industrial-grid absolute inset-0 opacity-10"></div>

      <div class="relative container mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <a href="/news" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[#FFC600] text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-8 hover:text-white transition-colors">
            &larr; BACK TO NEWSROOM
          </a>

          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
            <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-[#FFC600] tracking-widest bg-[#FFC600]/10 px-3 py-1 clip-corner">COLONIES</span>
            <span class="text-[10px] font-mono text-gray-600 tracking-wider">PRESS RELEASE</span>
          </div>

          <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black text-white uppercase leading-none mb-6">
            WEYLAND-YUTANI CELEBRATES <span class="text-[#FFC600]">300TH COLONY</span> MILESTONE
          </h1>

          <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-6 text-sm text-gray-500 font-mono">
            <span>JUNE 12, 2112</span>
            <span class="text-[#FFC600]">|</span>
            <span>SAN FRANCISCO, CA</span>
            <span class="text-[#FFC600]">|</span>
            <span>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-0 right-0 hazard-stripes-thin h-1"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- ARTICLE BODY -->
    <section class="relative py-16 bg-black">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
          <div class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed space-y-6 text-base">
            <p class="text-lg text-white font-semibold">
              <strong>SAN FRANCISCO --</strong> Weyland-Yutani Corporation (NYSE: WEYU) today announced the official commissioning of its 300th colony world, marking a milestone that reflects the Corporation's eight-decade commitment to expanding the frontiers of human civilization. The milestone colony, designated Covenant's Landing on the planet Eridani IV in the Epsilon Eridani system, received its certificate of permanent habitation from the Interstellar Commerce Commission at 0600 UTC.
            </p>

            <p>
              The achievement places Weyland-Yutani at the center of the greatest expansion of human settlement since the migrations of antiquity. From the first permanent off-world installation on Luna in 2031 to the thriving interstellar network of today, the Corporation has been the primary architect of humanity's presence beyond Earth.
            </p>

            <p>
              "Three hundred worlds," said CEO Karl Bishop Weyland. "Three hundred communities where human beings are living, working, raising families, and building futures. Every one of them exists because this Corporation had the vision to make it happen and the discipline to see it through."
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mt-12 mb-4">A HISTORY OF EXPANSION</h2>
            <div class="h-px w-24 bg-[#FFC600] mb-6"></div>

            <p>
              The Corporation's colonization program has followed a disciplined trajectory since its inception:
            </p>

            <div class="my-8 space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-[#0a0a0a] border-l-2 border-[#FFC600]">
                <span class="text-[#FFC600] font-mono font-bold text-sm shrink-0 w-16">2031</span>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">First permanent off-world settlement established on Luna (Sea of Tranquility)</p>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-[#0a0a0a] border-l-2 border-[#FFC600]">
                <span class="text-[#FFC600] font-mono font-bold text-sm shrink-0 w-16">2039</span>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">First breathable atmosphere created on an extrasolar world (GJ 667Cc)</p>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-[#0a0a0a] border-l-2 border-[#FFC600]">
                <span class="text-[#FFC600] font-mono font-bold text-sm shrink-0 w-16">2048</span>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">50th colony established; total off-world population exceeds 500,000</p>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-[#0a0a0a] border-l-2 border-[#FFC600]">
                <span class="text-[#FFC600] font-mono font-bold text-sm shrink-0 w-16">2072</span>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">100th colony milestone; colonization pace accelerates to 8 worlds per year</p>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-[#0a0a0a] border-l-2 border-[#FFC600]">
                <span class="text-[#FFC600] font-mono font-bold text-sm shrink-0 w-16">2093</span>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">200th colony; off-world population surpasses 12 million</p>
              </div>
              <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-4 bg-[#0a0a0a] border-l-2 border-[#FFC600]">
                <span class="text-[#FFC600] font-mono font-bold text-sm shrink-0 w-16">2112</span>
                <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">300th colony commissioned; off-world population exceeds 40 million</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <p>
              Today, the Corporation's colony network spans 14 star systems and supports a total off-world population of more than 40 million people. Colony economies contribute an estimated $1.8 trillion annually to interstellar commerce, with the largest installations -- including Thedus, Arcturus Station, and the Zeta Reticuli settlements -- functioning as self-sustaining economic centers.
            </p>

            <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-white uppercase mt-12 mb-4">CONTINUED EXPANSION</h2>
            <div class="h-px w-24 bg-[#FFC600] mb-6"></div>

            <p>
              Weyland-Yutani has confirmed plans to establish an additional 50 colony installations over the next decade, with a strategic focus on resource-rich systems in the Outer Veil sector. The Corporation is investing $340 billion in next-generation atmospheric processors capable of terraforming candidate worlds 40% faster than current technology allows.
            </p>

            <p>
              "The 300th colony is a milestone, not a destination," said Dr. Ines Alvarez, President of Colony Operations. "We are building the infrastructure for a civilization that will endure for millennia. Every colony is a foothold, every world a foundation."
            </p>

            <p>
              A commemorative event will be held at the Corporation's San Francisco headquarters on June 20, 2112, attended by colonial administrators, government officials, and members of the founding families of the earliest off-world settlements.
            </p>

            <!-- BOILERPLATE -->
            <div class="mt-16 pt-8 border-t border-[#1a1a1a]">
              <h3 class="text-sm font-black text-[#FFC600] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">ABOUT WEYLAND-YUTANI CORPORATION</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">
                Weyland-Yutani Corporation is a British-Japanese multinational conglomerate and the world's leading enterprise in terraforming, cybernetics, energy, health sciences, and interstellar colonization. With more than 500,000 employees across 47 countries and 300 colonized worlds, Weyland-Yutani is Building Better Worlds. NYSE: WEYU.
              </p>

              <h3 class="text-sm font-black text-[#FFC600] uppercase tracking-wider mb-4 mt-8">MEDIA CONTACT</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
                Corporate Communications<br/>
                media@weylandyutani.com<br/>
                +1-800-555-WYCO (9926)
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .clip-corner {
    clip-path: polygon(8px 0, 100% 0, 100% calc(100% - 8px), calc(100% - 8px) 100%, 0 100%, 0 8px);
  }
</style>
